# Security and Permissions Rules

<version>1.0.0</version>

## Context
- When implementing coupon CRUD operations
- When accessing user data
- When checking user permissions
- When validating input data
- When interacting with external APIs

## Requirements

### Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
- User role: Can only access own coupons
- Manager role: Can access all coupons and manage users
- Demo role: Read-only access to sample data
- Always check permissions in service layer before data access
- Never rely solely on client-side permission checks

### Ownership Verification
- Verify `userId` matches logged-in user before operations
- Check ownership in services, not components
- Throw descriptive error messages for access violations
- Implement RLS policies on database level (Supabase)

### Input Validation
- Validate all user inputs on client-side for UX
- Validate all user inputs on server-side for security
- Sanitize data before storage
- Use parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection
- Validate email format, phone numbers, etc.

### Data Security
- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens)
- Never expose service role keys in client code
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Mask partial sensitive data in logs
- Implement rate limiting on authentication endpoints

### Error Handling
- Never expose internal error details to users
- Use generic error messages for security-sensitive operations
- Log full error details server-side for debugging
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Handle network errors gracefully

## Examples

<example>
// ✅ Good: Ownership check in service
async getCoupon(id: string, userId?: string): Promise<Coupon | null> {
  const coupon = await this.db.getById(id);

  if (!coupon) {
    return null;
  }

  // Check ownership for user role
  if (userId && coupon.userId !== userId) {
    throw new Error('Access denied: You can only access your own coupons');
  }

  return coupon;
}

// ✅ Good: Role-based permission check
async getAllCoupons(user: User | null): Promise<Coupon[]> {
  if (!user) {
    throw new Error('Authentication required');
  }

  if (user.role === 'demo') {
    // Demo users get read-only sample data
    return getSampleCoupons();
  }

  if (user.role === 'user') {
    // Users see only their own coupons
    return this.db.query({ userId: user.id });
  }

  if (user.role === 'manager') {
    // Managers see all coupons
    return this.db.queryAll();
  }

  throw new Error('Invalid user role');
}

// ✅ Good: Input validation
async addCoupon(data: CouponFormData, userId?: string): Promise<Coupon> {
  if (!data.retailer?.trim()) {
    throw new Error('Retailer is required');
  }

  if (!data.initialValue?.trim()) {
    throw new Error('Initial value is required');
  }

  if (isNaN(parseFloat(data.initialValue))) {
    throw new Error('Initial value must be a number');
  }

  // ... proceed with safe data
}
</example>

<example type="invalid">
// ❌ Bad: No ownership check
async getCoupon(id: string): Promise<Coupon | null> {
  // Anyone can access any coupon!
  return this.db.getById(id);
}

// ❌ Bad: Client-side only validation
const addCoupon = (data) => {
  if (data.retailer) {
    // No server validation - security risk!
    api.post('/coupons', data);
  }
};

// ❌ Bad: Exposing sensitive data
console.log('User logged in:', {
  email: user.email,
  password: user.password, // NEVER log passwords!
  token: user.token // NEVER expose tokens in logs!
});

// ❌ Bad: Generic error without context
catch (error) {
  throw new Error('Something went wrong'); // Not helpful
}
</example>
